ntial School system, and Indigenous participation in the First World War. Mortensen’s insights and experiences will be of interest to scholars, students, and enthusiasts of the fur trade and contribute to literary, Indigenous, and Scandinavian studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFur tradezManitobaxHistoryy20th century. 0aFur traderszManitobaxHistoryy20th century. 0aFur traderszNorwayxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndigenous peopleszManitobaxHistoryy20th century. 4aCreative Writing / Auto/biography & Memoir. 4aCreative Writing. 4aHistory / Canadian History. 4aHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Indigenous Studies.2bisacsh  afur trade free trader Indigenous Oxford Lake Pine Bluff Scandinavian Norway Oslo narrative oral history primary document Pelshandleren Hudson’s Bay Company travel journey voyageur trapper beaver.1 aKjustad Mortensen, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMortensen, Gerd Kjustad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSims, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSims, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUrberg, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUrberg, Ingrid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212615040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772126150423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772126150/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-d